abstract.text: A description of the edits made to an asset’s photo, video, or Live Photo content, which allows your app to reconstruct or revert the effects of prior editing sessions.

inlineContent.text: When a user edits an asset, Photos saves a

object along with the modified image or video data. This object provides an application-defined “recipe” you can use to reconstruct the edit. For example, if your app applies filters to a photo, you might create adjustment data that identifies which filters the user picked, the parameters for each, and the order to apply the filters in. Later, the user can resume working with those filters and parameters by using your app or another app that understands your adjustment data format. When iCloud Photos is enabled, a user can revert or resume edits made on a different device.
